    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;">how to use old sdk dart of package with newer sdk dart of main flutter  </div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
    background-color: #fff3e6;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>To use an older version of a Dart package with a newer version of Flutter, you can follow these steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Open your <code>pubspec.yaml</code> file in your Flutter project.</li>
<li>Find the package that you want to use an older version of. It will be listed under the <code>dependencies</code> section.</li>
<li>Add the package as a dependency with the desired version. For example, if the package is named <code>example_package</code> and you want to use version <code>1.0.0</code>, add the following line:<br />
<code>yaml
   example_package: ^1.0.0</code><br />
   Note the <code>^</code> symbol, which means you want to use any version within the <code>1.0.0</code> range. If you want to use a specific version, omit the <code>^</code> symbol and specify the version number directly.</li>
<li>Run the command <code>flutter pub get</code> in your project directory to fetch the package and its dependencies. This command ensures that the specified version is downloaded and added to your project.</li>
</ol>
<p>Now, you can import the package as you normally would in your code, and the older version will be used instead of the newer version provided by Flutter.</p>
<p>However, it's important to keep in mind that using old versions of packages could lead to compatibility issues or missing out on new features and bug fixes. Therefore, it's generally recommended to update your dependencies to the latest versions whenever possible.</p></div>

